# ponder:  the Python API to your data anywhere

Ponder lets you run pandas workflows directly in your database, meaning that you get
all the scalability and security benefits of your database, while still preserving the
[ease-of-use](https://ponder.io/pandas-vs-sql-part-4-pandas-is-more-convenient) and
[flexibility](https://ponder.io/pandas-vs-sql-part-3-pandas-is-more-flexible) of pandas.

Ponder builds on top of the open source project
[Modin](https://github.com/modin-project/modin), with added support for commercial data
warehouses, tailored to the needs of production workloads in enterprise settings.

Visit [app.ponder.io](https://app.ponder.io) to sign up.

